{"type":"text","timestamp":1773481784950,"sessionID":"ses_314408df1ffewl9iPH4Mn42Qn5","part":{"id":"prt_cebc060d4001aRP9q08M0BF5FX","sessionID":"ses_314408df1ffewl9iPH4Mn42Qn5","messageID":"msg_cebc05737001Is6gcg21wd5xBl","type":"text","text":"Now I have the key insight from the log. The actual `step_finish` event from opencode has this token structure:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"step_finish\",\n  \"part\": {\n    \"reason\": \"tool-calls\" | \"stop\",\n    \"cost\": 0,\n    \"tokens\": {\n      \"total\": 21672,\n      \"input\": 513,\n      \"output\": 202,\n      \"reasoning\": 0,\n      \"cache\": {\n        \"read\": 20957,\n        \"write\": 0\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nNow I can see the actual shape. The existing `OpenCodeEvent` interface has `tokens` with `total`, `input`, `output`, `reasoning` but is **missing** the `cache` sub-object. Let me also check if there's a model field on events:","time":{"start":1773481784950,"end":1773481784950}}}
