{"type":"text","timestamp":1773481945498,"sessionID":"ses_314408df1ffewl9iPH4Mn42Qn5","part":{"id":"prt_cebc2d7fd001rGRFbja5X1SGqH","sessionID":"ses_314408df1ffewl9iPH4Mn42Qn5","messageID":"msg_cebc2cd040016vYrHayjFe0m5g","type":"text","text":"Wait, the `getRecords` check isn't the right way to see if an agent is registered. Let me look at what the TokenCollector class exposes. The records map would return an empty array even if registered. Let me use a different approach - just always register (registerAgent is idempotent):\n\nActually, looking at `registerAgent`, it initializes an empty records array if not present and sets context. If we call it again, it would overwrite context. Let me just always call it with no context as a fallback:","time":{"start":1773481945498,"end":1773481945498}}}
