{"type":"text","timestamp":1773481953462,"sessionID":"ses_314408df1ffewl9iPH4Mn42Qn5","part":{"id":"prt_cebc2fecb0012t8QGN7yimhlH1","sessionID":"ses_314408df1ffewl9iPH4Mn42Qn5","messageID":"msg_cebc2f5f8001akM3EvvlXuf3hP","type":"text","text":"The `ingestEvent` method already handles the case where an agent isn't registered - it creates the records array on demand. So no explicit registration needed in `addProcess`. The caller can optionally pre-register with context via `monitor.tokenCollector.registerAgent()`. This is cleaner.\n\nNow let me also update the `formatEventForLog` function to include cache info when available:","time":{"start":1773481953462,"end":1773481953462}}}
