{"type":"text","timestamp":1773482032224,"sessionID":"ses_314408df1ffewl9iPH4Mn42Qn5","part":{"id":"prt_cebc416cb001I07da1WNJ1afVp","sessionID":"ses_314408df1ffewl9iPH4Mn42Qn5","messageID":"msg_cebc40b79001tneziACygtXcXI","type":"text","text":"Everything passes. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n## Summary\n\n### Task: Parse token usage from agent output events (`token-parse`)\n\n**Two commits on `feature/token-parse`:**\n\n1. **`a15077a` — Add UsageRecord type, TokenCollector class, and update OpenCodeEvent tokens shape**\n   - Created `src/lib/token-collector.ts` with:\n     - `UsageRecord` type with all required fields: `task_id`, `quest_id`, `model`, `provider`, `harness`, `input_tokens`, `output_tokens`, `cache_read`, `cache_write`, `reasoning_tokens`, `total_tokens`, `cost`, `is_final_step`, `timestamp`\n     - `UsageSummary` type for aggregated per-agent totals\n     - `isTokenEvent()` — checks if an event has token data\n     - `parseUsageFromEvent()` — extracts a `UsageRecord` from a `step_finish` event\n     - `TokenCollector` class with `registerAgent()`, `ingestEvent()`, `getRecords()`, `getSummary()`, `getAllSummaries()`, `clear()`, `clearAll()`\n   - Updated `OpenCodeEvent.part.tokens` in `monitor.ts` to include `cache?: { read: number; write: number }` matching actual opencode JSON output\n\n2. **`cdb6b6b` — Integrate TokenCollector into ProcessMonitor**\n   - Added `onUsage` callback to `MonitorCallbacks` interface\n   - Instantiated `TokenCollector` in `ProcessMonitor` constructor, wired to `onUsage` callback\n   - Added `tokenCollector.ingestEvent()` call in the stdout event parsing loop\n   - Exposed `tokenCollector` as a public property for direct access\n   - Enhanced `formatEventForLog` to display cache read counts on final step\n   - Re-exported `UsageRecord`, `UsageSummary`, `UsageCallback`, `TokenCollector` from `monitor.ts`","time":{"start":1773482032223,"end":1773482032223}}}
